<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Mansouri     03-09 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Mansouri,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toronto Opera Chief Offered SF Job</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lofti Mansouri, head of the Canadian Opera
in Toronto, has been offered the job of general director of the San
Francisco Opera.
   Mansouri has been a leading candidate for the position since
Terence A. McEwen announced on Feb. 9 that he would retire.
   ``They have offered it and I am considering it very seriously,''
Mansouri said Tuesday in a telephone interview from Toronto. He
said he would make a decision by Friday.
   The San Francisco Opera Association's board of directors on
Tuesday accepted the recomendation of a subcommittee and authorized
that the job be offered to Mansouri.
   Mansouri, 58, a native of Iran, has directed 31 productions for
the San Francisco opera on a visiting basis since 1963.
</TEXT>
