<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Britain-Lesbians,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Women Chain Selves To Buckingham Palace Gates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five self-proclaimed lesbians were arrested for
chaining themselves to Buckingham Palace's gates to protest the
government's plan to stop giving public funds to homosexual groups.
   Police cut the women free from the gates after a half-hour and
took them into custody.
   The demonstrators said their action Tuesday coincided with the
70th anniversary of suffragettes doing the same in the campaign to
win votes for women. Twelve female supporters, some in Victorian
clothing, paraded on the sidewalk.
   The demonstration was against a government bill that would make
local councils stop funding homosexual groups or promoting
homosexuality as a legitimate lifestyle.
   ``We chose the palace because the bill will have to gain royal
assent next month before it becomes law,'' said one of the women,
who refused to give her name.
</TEXT>
