<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan Markets,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Closes Higher Against Yen; Stocks Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar rose slightly in Tokyo on Wednesday,
while stock prices gained substantially following an overnight
advance on Wall Street.
   The dollar closed at 128.08 yen, up 0.28 yen from Tuesday's
close. It opened at 127.80 yen and ranged between 127.73 yen and
128.27 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the 225-share Nikkei Stock Average,
which lost 150.85 points Tuesday, gained back 139.66 points, or
0.55 percent, closing at 25,605.39. Trading was relatively heavy at
1.3 billion shares.
   Michio Katsumata of Nomura Securities, Japan's largest brokerage
house, said Tokyo stock prices were supported by Tuesday's rally on
the New York Stock Exchange and by stabilization of the foreign
exchange market.
   Investors also appeared to be buying shares deemed to be at
bargain prices after the Tokyo market's decline on Tuesday, dealers
said.
</TEXT>
