<HEAD>Military Copters Collide Over Kentucky, All 17 Aboard Believed
Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT CAMPBELL, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two military helicopters collided
during a night training mission, and all 17 aboard the crafts were
believed killed, an official said.
   The crash occurred late Tuesday, 6 miles from Fort Campbell Army
air field, said Randy Schoel, a military spokesman.
   He said the crash occurred during a ``routine night mission,''
and that all 17 aboard were believed killed.
   The identification of the victims was not complete.
