<TEXT>
   Home states smiled on four out of five
favorite sons on Super Tuesday.
   In nearly complete returns, Gov. Michael Dukakis won 59 percent
of the votes in the primary in Massachusetts, his home turf.
   Albert Gore won 72 percent in his native state of Tennessee.
   Richard Gephardt won 58 percent in the friendly surroundings of
Missouri.
   George Bush carried his adopted state of Texas with 64 percent.
   But Pat Robertson won only 15 percent in his state of Virginia.
Bush carried the Old Dominion with 53 percent.
