<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>FRANKFURT, West Germany, television reported</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The Christian Democratic politician died in the Tuebingen
University hospital of heart failure, the ARD television network
said on its 1 p.m. newscast.
   Kiesinger served as West Germany's third chancellor, from 1966
to 1969.
   He grouped together the Christian Democrats and their Bavarian
counterparts with the leftist-leaning Social Democrats (SPD) to
form what is called the ``Grand Coalition.'' Willy Brandt served as
the coalition's foreign minister, before taking over as chancellor.
</TEXT>
