<HEAD>Nine Black Policmen Injured In Grenade and Rifle Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Attackers hurling hand
grenades and firing automatic rifles assaulted a police station in
Soweto and injured nine black officers, police headquarters said
today.
   The assailants fled in a vehicle after policemen returned fire
with shotguns, according to police. No arrested were reported.
   The attack occurred Tuesday night as municipal policemen were
changing shifts at the Mapetla police station in Soweto,
Johannesburg's main black township.
   Police said the attackers threw three hand grenades at the
officers and fired Soviet-made AK-47 rifles. Only one of the
wounded officers was seriously hurt, police said.
   Black policemen have been frequent targets of attacks by
anti-apartheid militants who view them as government collaborators.
   Authorities have blamed many previous attacks on the outlawed
African National Congress guerrilla movement.
