   That means a $9 dollar bet on Bush would net $4 plus the
original stake.
   Next in line was Democrat Michael Dukakis at 4-1, followed by
Sen. Robert Dole, R-Kan., at 8-1. New York Gov. Mario Cuomo, a
Democrat, fetched odds of 10-1 despite staying out of the race.
Sen. Albert Gore, D-Tenn., was quoted at 11-1, the Rev. Jesse
Jackson at 20-1 and Rep. Richard Gephardt, D-Mo., at 50-1.
