<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BanditBitesBaker     03-09 0228</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bandit Bites Baker,0231</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bandit Battles Baker But Is Bested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST VALLEY CITY, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman armed with a toy gun
failed in an attempt to rob a doughnut shop, but bit the baker who
subdued her, police said.
   Police arrived at the Winchell's Donut House Tuesday to find the
``exhausted'' 59-year-old baker, Jay Anderson, holding a
36-year-old woman down on the floor, the police report said.
   The woman entered the shop at about 4 a.m. and bought a
chocolate doughnut. When the baker opened the cash register, the
woman pulled a gun from under her jacket and said ``Give me all of
it or I'll kill you,'' the report said.
   Anderson stood back and told her to take the money herself.
While the woman had her hands in the till, he grabbed her and
pulled her across the counter. The gun, which Anderson believed to
be real, came out of the woman's hand and broke apart.
   After wrestling with the woman for what ``seemed like forever,''
the baker said he got to the phone and called police. Meanwhile,
the woman was kicking and punching him continuously, and also
``took a bite out of his arm,'' the report said.
   Anderson was treated at a nearby hospital and released. Police
said the woman would be charged with aggravated robbery, but
refused to release her name immediately.
</TEXT>
