<1ST_LINE>d a PM-Obit-Reed 1stLd-Writethru a0846 03-09 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Reed, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0846,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Radio and TV Performer, Columnist Tobe Reed Dead at 76</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf to fix garble</NOTE>
<DATELINE>RANCHO MIRAGE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tobe Reed, former radio and
television performer and newspaper columnist, has died at the age
of 76.
   Reed died March 3 at Eisenhower Memorial Hospital in this desert
resort town.
   Reed hosted TV's ``Top Dollar'' game show in the 1950s and
performed with George Burns and Gracie Allen on their radio show.
He also was heard on the radio programs ``Fitch's Bandwagon'' and
``Duffy's Tavern.''
   Reed also worked as a columnist for the San Francisco Chronicle.
He was born in Seattle on Christmas Day 1911.
   Reed is survived by his wife, Mary Elizabeth; a son, Tobe Jr.; a
daughter, Melinda, and two grandsons.
   Rancho Mirage is about 10 miles southeast of Palm Springs, about
120 miles southeast of downtown Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
