<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Fire     03-09 0081</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Italy-Fire,0083</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Woman Killed, Four People Badly Burned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TRIESTE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through an apartment building
housing mental patients, killing a 64-year-old woman and seriously
injuring four other people, firefighters said.
   The fire, possibly originating in a stove, broke out in a
third-floor apartment where several patients had been living since
1975 under a reform providing their treatment outside hospitals.
   The dead woman was identified as Maria Svagel, who was trapped
by the flames in her bed.
</TEXT>
