<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Fugitive Recaptured,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Most Wanted Fugitive Caught In Brooklyn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convicted rapist who was placed on the U.S.
Marshal Service's 15 most wanted list after twice escaping from
county jails was recaptured after seven months on the run,
authorities said.
   Garnett R. Leacock, 38, offered no resistance when marshals
acting on a tip arrested him Tuesday at a Brooklyn apartment, said
Frank Peo, marshal for the northern district of New York.
   Leacock escaped Aug. 9 from the Montgomery County Jail in Fonda,
where he was awaiting sentencing in the rape of a 16-year-old girl
at his home at Griffiss Air Force Base in Rome, authorities said.
He was sentenced in abstentia to 27 years.
   In July, Leacock escaped from the Madison County Jail by digging
a hole in the wall of his cell and slipping through after lathering
his body with shampoo. He was recaptured two days later after his
wife, who aided in both escapes, turned him in after having second
thoughts, authorities said.
   Air Force Sgt. Deborah Leacock is serving a five-year sentence
for her role in the second escape.
</TEXT>
