<2ND_LINE>AM-Albany Shooting,0256</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Dead, Two Others Wounded in Downtown Shootings</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto AB2</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DIANNE HENK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six men were arrested Wednesday on the New
York State Thruway after a downtown shooting that left one man dead
and two others seriously injured, police said.
   The three men were shot shortly after 8 a.m. in a second-floor
apartment, said police Sgt. Bob Wolfgang. One victim, who was
critically injured, managed to flee the apartment and call police,
Wolfgang said.
   The wounded men, both in their 20s, underwent surgery at Albany
Medical Center Hospital, said hospital spokesman Greg McGarry.
Their identities were not released.
   The man who was in critical condition suffered multiple wounds
to the head and neck, McGarry said.
   Wolfgang would not say if the shootings were drug-related, but
said a drug raid had taken place earlier in the morning at a nearby
residence. Automatic weapons and a shotgun were apparently used in
the shootings, he said.
   About two hours after the shooting, state police stopped a sedan
about 70 miles south of Albany, said State Police Sgt. William
Nolan. The car was carrying six men who were taken into custody,
said Maj. Wayne Bennett. They were taken to the Loudonville state
police barracks and were being questioned, but no names were
immediately released.
   A woman who apparently was at the apartment at the time of the
shooting was also taken to the hospital for observation,
authorities said. She had not been shot.
