<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--EEC-Israel     03-09 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--EEC-Israel,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>European Parliament Rejects EEC Deal with Israel</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STRASBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Parliament on Wednesday
rejected a European Economic Community financial aid package for
Israel in a protest of the nation's treatment of Palestinians in
the occupied territories.
   By a 205-143 vote, the Parliament rejected the EEC's agreement
to provide Israel with low-interest development loans of up to
$76.9 million in the next four years.
   In separate votes, the Parliament turned down two minor accords
updating the EEC's treaties on the sale of Israeli farm produce in
Europe.
   This is the first time the Parliament has rejected EEC
agreements since it was given the power last year to ratify foreign
treaties.
   All three documents will have to go back to the 12 Common Market
capitals for renegotiation, which could delay implementation for
several months.
   The vote represents a sharp rebuke to Israel for its policy in
the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip.
   Many deputies also criticized Israel for breaching an unrelated
pledge to allow Palestinians to export their farm produce directly
to Europe. Instead, all Palestinian exports must be channeled
through Israeli authorities.
</TEXT>
