<HEAD>Libertyville Weekly Goes Daily</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIBERTYVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new daily newspaper debuts Monday
when the South West News-Sun, a weekly newspaper for 96 years,
begins publishing six days a week.
   The News-Sun will report community news and sports in
Libertyville, Mundelein and Vernon Hills, as well as state and
national news, said Publisher Glenn Pfeil.
   The South West News-Sun is affiliated with Copley Press, whose
Illinois holdings also include the Aurora Beacon-News, Elgin
Courier News, Joliet Herald-News, Lincoln Courier, Springfield
Journal-Register, Wheaton Daily Journal and its sister newspaper,
The News-Sun of Waukegan.
   To accommodate the changes, the newspaper has added five new
editorial positions, three advertising representatives, and
additional office and circulation department personnel, said Jan
Gehrig, managing editor.
