<2ND_LINE>AM-Crops-Oranges,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Orange Crop Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's orange harvest for the 1987-88
crop season is estimated at 199.6 million boxes, 3 percent more
than forecast in February and 10 percent more than last year, the
Agriculture Department said Wednesday.
   Florida production, based on March 1 indications, was estimated
at 140 million boxes, up 4 percent from February and 17 percent
more than last season's crop.
   The California harvest was estimated at 55 million boxes, up 2
percent from February's forecast but 6 percent less than in
1986-87. The Arizona crop was indicated at 3.05 million boxes,
unchanged from February and down 3 percent from last season.
   Texas production, at 1.55 million boxes, was unchanged from last
month's forecast but was up 77 percent from 1986-87's harvest of
875,000 boxes.
</TEXT>
