<HEAD>Reagan Signs Executive Order On Nuclear Cooperation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan signed an executive order
Wednesday allowing continued cooperation with European nations on
peaceful nuclear energy matters.
   The document extends more than two decades of cooperation
between the United States and the European Atomic Energy Community
(EURATOM).
