<HEAD>Police Sent to Quell Religious Violence at Nigerian School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Riot police closed a technical school in
the mainly Moslem north Wednesday after students there destroyed a
Christian chapel, newspapers reported.
   Ten pupils were hurt when more than 10,000 students fled the
campus of Kaduna Polytechnic school because of the arrival of the
armed police, the Lagos newspapers reported.
   Christian students demonstrated Wednesday in the streets of
Kaduna, where riot police were out in force. There were several
violent incidents and one injury, the reports said without
elaborating.
   Kaduna is about 375 miles northeast of the Nigerian capital of
Lagos.
   On Tuesday, a group of Moslem students marched on a Christian
chapel under construction at the technical school. The students
smashed the walls, causing the structure to collapse, the newspaper
reports said.
   Christian students had been asking authorities to build the
chapel for more than 10 years. There are five Moslem mosques at the
school.
   Southern Nigeria, where the capital city of Lagos is located, is
primarily Christian.
