profit-sharing checks to U.S. workers as their share of the
company's industry record profit of $4.6 billion for 1987.
   Ford distributed $653 million in profit-sharing checks Tuesday
averaging more than $3,700 to 156,479 hourly and salaried workers.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cheating on federal income taxes has declined
by as much as 20 percent, mainly because of tax law changes and
tougher federal policing, Internal Revenue Service Commissioner
Lawrence B. Gibbs says.
   Gibbs told a House Appropriations subcommittee on Tuesday that
an IRS study indicates the difference between taxes owed and taxes
paid has dropped to between $80 billion and $90 billion in 1987.
The agency's last report on the annual gap estimated it would rise
to more than $100 billion in 1987.
</TEXT>
