<TEXT>
   The average college administrator got a 3.3
percent pay increase this year, down from a 5.3 percent increase a
year ago, the College and University Personnel Association says.
   The 3.3 percent increase for 1987-88 was less than the 3.7
percent increase in consumer prices during the same period, and the
first time since 1982-83 that the college salaries trailed the rise
in the Consumer Price Index.
   The association said Tuesday it derived the figures from its
11th annual survey of how much colleges pay their presidents, deans
and administrators.
