<1ST_LINE>r f BC-EEC-CentralBank     03-09 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Central Bank,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kohl Calls Creation EEC Central Bank `Absolute Necessity'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STRASBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
Wednesday called the creation of a European central bank an
``absolute necessity.''
   But he told the European Parliament that fusing the monetary
policies of the 12 European Economic Community nations must be
``gradual, step by step.''
   Kohl's backing of an EEC central bank was more cautious than
that of his foreign minister, Hans-Dietrich Genshcer, who last
month called for the creation of an experts group to see how such a
central bank could be formed.
   Genscher suggested the experts be named by the next EEC summit
in June with the mandate of drafting within a year the statutes of
an EEC central bank.
   EEC business leaders also have called for the creation of a
European central bank.
</TEXT>
