<1ST_LINE>r f BC-DisneySuit     03-09 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Disney Suit,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Disney Files Trademark Infringement Suit on Mickey Mouse Phones</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Walt Disney Co. has filed a copyright and
trademark infringement suit accusing more than 15 outlets in New
York City of unauthorized distribution and sale of toy telephones
bearing a likeness of Mickey Mouse.
   The suit, filed Wednesday in U.S. District Court for the
Southern District of New York, is the latest of a rash of legal
actions brought by the Burbank-based entertainment concern for
alleged unauthorized use of Disney characters.
   In the past 24 months, the company has brought 14 suits
involving more than 400 manufacturers, distributors and retailers
in New York, South Carolina, Florida, Texas, California and
Washington, D.C., the Burbank, Calif.-based company said.
   Disney's latest action asks the court to award unspecified
damages and to enjoin the distributors and stores from importing
and selling the telephones with the unauthorized Mickey Mouse
likenesses.
</TEXT>
